messages.content: What is the purpose of the comfyui-parse-image custom node?
The purpose of the comfyui-parse-image custom node is to extract metadata from images in ComfyUI.
What are the different types of loader nodes available in comfyui-parse-image?
The different types of loader nodes available in comfyui-parse-image are Load Boolean From Image, Load Int From Image, Load Float From Image, Load String From Image, and Load Combo From Image.
Which image node types are supported by comfyui-parse-image?
The supported image node types in comfyui-parse-image are LoadImage, LoadImage //Inspire, Load image with metadata [Crystools], Image Load, and PutImage.
How should the comfyui-parse-image node be connected in a flow?
The comfyui-parse-image node must be connected to a flow started by a supported image node.
What is the query format used in comfyui-parse-image?
The query format used in comfyui-parse-image is <TITLE|TYPE|ID>.<WIDGET_NAME>
What are some examples of queries that can be used with comfyui-parse-image?
Some example queries that can be used with comfyui-parse-image are Load Checkpoint.ckpt_name, CheckpointLoaderSimple.ckpt_name, 1.ckpt_name, and KSampler.seed.
What special format queries are available in comfyui-parse-image?
The special format queries available in comfyui-parse-image are width and height.
Where can one find more information about ComfyUI custom scripts?
More information about ComfyUI custom scripts can be found in the GitHub repository ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts.
